      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Galactose, a constituent of the disaccharide lactose found in dairy products, is metabolized by a pathway that includes the isomerization of UDP-galactose to UDP-glucose, where UDP = uridylyl diphosphate. The enzyme responsible for the transformation uses NAD<sup>+</sup> as cofactor. Propose a mechanism.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ1VXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--6485b3fa9769f510d16872d65c445a04b7a05565/OChem_17_EC_053.jpg\" alt=\"The compound, U D P-galactose isomerizes to form U D P-glucose.\">",
